HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karin mutane 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne ke fama da cutar a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane 40,000.
A bambanci da baya, yawancin sabbin masu kamuwa da cutar sun kamu ne ta hanyar jima'i.
A yanzu, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon ƙarin jini da aka yi wa mutane.
Amma, adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
Amma a shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya ƙaru da 100,000 a ƙasar Sin.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a China.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma ana nuna wa 'yan kungiyar LGBT nuna wariya sosai.
Saboda tsattsauran ra'ayin kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza suna aure.
Yawancin cututtukan da ake samu daga jima'i suna faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya a lokacin jima'i.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa da kowa don magance matsalar.
